{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"hpnaglyhnb48vuiniqecnqf","title":"Nginx","desc":"","updated":1655630224645,"created":1655621752930,"custom":{},"fname":"nginx","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"783c58417e09fe519a031fd2e02d6fd2","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"nginx","id":"hpnaglyhnb48vuiniqecnqf","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.biolpc045600","alias":"@biolpc045600","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":16,"offset":808},"end":{"line":29,"column":29,"offset":821},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.biolpc045600"}}],"anchors":{"title":{"type":"header","text":"Title","value":"title","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1},"context":{"type":"header","text":"Context","value":"context","line":10,"column":0,"depth":2},"need":{"type":"header","text":"Need","value":"need","line":15,"column":0,"depth":2},"task-of-the-noteparagraphtextpaperproject":{"type":"header","text":"Task (of the note/paragraph/text/paper/project)","value":"task-of-the-noteparagraphtextpaperproject","line":18,"column":0,"depth":2},"if-you-would-like-to-gzip-your-stuff":{"type":"header","text":"If you would like to gzip your stuff","value":"if-you-would-like-to-gzip-your-stuff","line":95,"column":0,"depth":1},"setup-the-proxy":{"type":"header","text":"Setup the proxy","value":"setup-the-proxy","line":100,"column":0,"depth":1},"this-will-forward-all-requests-to-the-server":{"type":"header","text":"This will forward all requests to the server","value":"this-will-forward-all-requests-to-the-server","line":101,"column":0,"depth":1},"and-then-it-will-relay-the-servers-response-back-to-the-client":{"type":"header","text":"and then it will relay the servers response back to the client","value":"and-then-it-will-relay-the-servers-response-back-to-the-client","line":102,"column":0,"depth":1},"object-of-the-noteparagraphtextpaperproject":{"type":"header","text":"Object (of the note/paragraph/text/paper/project)","value":"object-of-the-noteparagraphtextpaperproject","line":130,"column":0,"depth":2},"ressources":{"type":"header","text":"Ressources","value":"ressources","line":134,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"QvYK9hGbCvPpEfSRYhV8j","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"nginx\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#nginx\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Nginx</h1>\n<h1 id=\"title\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#title\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Title</h1>\n<p>time</p>\n<h2 id=\"context\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#context\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Context</h2>\n<p>Looking into nginx to setup a connection to NocoDB from the commons_lab server </p>\n<p>This was done on the metabomaps server for the graphDB instance with the help of Jo.\nTrying to reproduce here.</p>\n<h2 id=\"need\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#need\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Need</h2>\n<p>setup a connection to NocoDB from the commons_lab server</p>\n<h2 id=\"task-of-the-noteparagraphtextpaperproject\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#task-of-the-noteparagraphtextpaperproject\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Task (of the note/paragraph/text/paper/project)</h2>\n<p>Third, indicate what you have done in an effort to address the need (this is the task).</p>\n<ul class=\"contains-task-list\">\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> Watching <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JKxlsvZXG7c\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JKxlsvZXG7c</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>They indicate that the conf file is usually under etc/nginx.\nIndeed over there on the metabomaps server.</p>\n<p>Lets looks at the commonslab server\nNot there.</p>\n<p>Lets install this</p>\n<p>Following <a href=\"https://ubuntu.com/tutorials/install-and-configure-nginx#2-installing-nginx\">https://ubuntu.com/tutorials/install-and-configure-nginx#2-installing-nginx</a></p>\n<p>We get the following error when starting nginx </p>\n<p>(base) allardpm<a title=\"Private\" style=\"color: brown\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\">@biolpc045600 (Private)</a>:/etc/nginx/sites-enabled$ systemctl status nginx.service\n● nginx.service - A high performance web server and a reverse proxy server\nLoaded: loaded (/lib/systemd/system/nginx.service; enabled; vendor preset: enabled)\nActive: failed (Result: exit-code) since Sun 2022-06-19 09:06:20 CEST; 57s ago\nDocs: man:nginx(8)\nProcess: 3544101 ExecStartPre=/usr/sbin/nginx -t -q -g daemon on; master_process on; (code=exited, status=0/SUCCESS)\nProcess: 3544102 ExecStart=/usr/sbin/nginx -g daemon on; master_process on; (code=exited, status=1/FAILURE)</p>\n<p>Following <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/51525710/nginx-failed-to-start-a-high-performance-web-server-and-a-reverse-proxy-server\">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/51525710/nginx-failed-to-start-a-high-performance-web-server-and-a-reverse-proxy-server</a></p>\n<p>we\nsudo service apache2 stop</p>\n<p> <img src=\"/commons-dws-public/assets/images/2022-06-19-09-11-18.png\"></p>\n<p> Amazing !</p>\n<ul class=\"contains-task-list\">\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> So this was a first step.\nApparently certbot was used later one. Lets see how this one works</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://certbot.eff.org/instructions?ws=nginx&#x26;os=ubuntufocal\">https://certbot.eff.org/instructions?ws=nginx&#x26;os=ubuntufocal</a></p>\n<p>I added the ip of the commons lab server to the dbgi DNS\nAnd can now vie the previously made placeholder website when serving on port 80</p>\n<p><img src=\"/commons-dws-public/assets/images/2022-06-19-09-43-57.png\"></p>\n<p>However the certbot step is not working\nsudo certbot --nginx</p>\n<p>And returns </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://check-your-website.server-daten.de/?q=commons.dbgi.org\">https://check-your-website.server-daten.de/?q=commons.dbgi.org</a></p>\n<p><img src=\"/commons-dws-public/assets/images/2022-06-19-10-53-34.png\"></p>\n<p>Yeah !! But thats on the metabomaps server. Apparently thing will not work that smoothly on the commons server sinc it is behind the university firewall\nrunning (saved as a .sh script)\ncertbot --authenticator standalone --installer nginx   -d xxxxxxx.xxxx.org --pre-hook \"service nginx stop\" --post-hook \"service nginx start\"</p>\n<ul class=\"contains-task-list\">\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> So I can serve the nocodb instance hosted on the commonslab server via a .dbgi.org domains</li>\n</ul>\n<p>nginx server file is as follows</p>\n<p>server {\nlisten 80;\nlisten [::]:80;</p>\n<pre><code>   server_name xxxxx.dbgi.org;\n</code></pre>\n<h1 id=\"if-you-would-like-to-gzip-your-stuff\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#if-you-would-like-to-gzip-your-stuff\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>If you would like to gzip your stuff</h1>\n<p>  gzip on;\ngzip_min_length 1;\ngzip_types *;</p>\n<h1 id=\"setup-the-proxy\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#setup-the-proxy\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Setup the proxy</h1>\n<h1 id=\"this-will-forward-all-requests-to-the-server\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#this-will-forward-all-requests-to-the-server\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>This will forward all requests to the server</h1>\n<h1 id=\"and-then-it-will-relay-the-servers-response-back-to-the-client\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#and-then-it-will-relay-the-servers-response-back-to-the-client\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>and then it will relay the servers response back to the client</h1>\n<p>  location / {\nproxy_pass <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8080\">http://127.0.0.1:8080</a>;\nproxy_http_version 1.1;\nproxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;\nproxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';\nproxy_set_header Host $host;\nproxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;\nproxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;\n}\n}</p>\n<p>Node: <strong>v16.15.1</strong>\nArch: <strong>x64</strong>\nPlatform: <strong>linux</strong>\nDocker: <strong>false</strong>\nDatabase: <strong>pg</strong>\nProjectOnRootDB: <strong>true</strong>\nRootDB: <strong>pg</strong>\nPackageVersion: <strong>0.91.10</strong></p>\n<h2 id=\"object-of-the-noteparagraphtextpaperproject\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#object-of-the-noteparagraphtextpaperproject\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Object (of the note/paragraph/text/paper/project)</h2>\n<p>Finally, preview the remainder of the paper to mentally prepare you/readers for its structure, in the object of the document.</p>\n<h2 id=\"ressources\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#ressources\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Ressources</h2>\n<p>Some notes:\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JKxlsvZXG7c\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JKxlsvZXG7c</a></p>","noteIndex":{"id":"QvYK9hGbCvPpEfSRYhV8j","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1630130450048,"created":1630130450048,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"c871f8270cbaf4ba23c0747ae826676a","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-dendron":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to Dendron","value":"welcome-to-dend